
[1]whet-slate

   WHETSTONE-SLATE, WHET-SLATE, n. Novaculite or coticular shist, a
   variety of slate used for sharpening instruments of iron. The light
   green colored variety from the Levant is the most valuable. It should
   be kept in a damp place, that it may not become too dry and hard.
